  • Method Details

    • toString

      public String toString()
      Allows getting a string representation of the wrapped executable. Using special methods in Class, Implementor and getImplementation() it generates signature and implementation of provided executable.
      Specified by:
      toString in class Record
      Returns:
      A string representation of the wrapped executable (constructor or method)
      See Also:
      • Executable

    • getImplementation

      private String getImplementation()
      Serializes executable implementation.
      Returns:
      • in the case of methods, the return value is a string representation of the implementation of the method, exactly the return of the default value
      • in the case of constructors, the return value is a string representation of the implementation of the constructor, exactly calling the superclass constructor with same arguments
      • otherwise ""
      See Also:
      • Implementor.getDefaultValue(Class)
      • Implementor.getArguments(Executable, boolean)
      • Executable
